I actually think this could become one of the more original parts of Pantheon if you avoid treating archetypes as the ontology itself.

The insight I'd build around is:

> **Humans don't think in vectors. They think in stories.**
>
> The latent space is computationally useful. The symbolic layer is cognitively useful.

That immediately suggests a two-layer cognitive architecture.

```
